Paul R. JERABEK, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 25648. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. May 20, 1968. Rehearing Denied July 3, 1968. *829Frank A. Pavese, Fort Myers, Fla., for appellant. Thomas G. Wilson, Asst. U. S. Atty., Tampa, Fla., Edward F. Boardman, U. S. Atty. Middle District of Florida, for ap-pellee.

Before POPE,* TUTTLE and CLAYTON, Circuit Judges.

Of the Ninth Circuit, sitting by designation.

 PER CURIAM:

There having been sufficient evidence upon which the jury was warranted to find beyond a reasonable doubt that the appellant was guilty of violating Section 501(c) of Title 29 U.S.C., the judgment is

Affirmed.
